{"timestamp": "2025-12-07 04:46:18.877375", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nExecutive summary\\n- Network health: Degraded. End hosts cannot obtain IP addresses or reach server-farm services. The server-farm network (10.200.0.0/24) is isolated from the OSPF domain.\\n- Primary anomalies:\\n  1) DHCP relays on both distribution routers are not running, so host subnets do not get DHCP service.\\n  2) The server_access_router is not participating in OSPF, so 10.200.0.0/24 is not advertised into the campus, leaving no route to the DHCP/DNS/Web farm from the rest of the network.\\n\\nEvidence and findings\\n\\n1) End hosts lack IP configuration and routes\\n- host_1_1_1_1 and host_2_1_1_1 have link up on eth0 but no IPv4 address and no routing table.\\n  • host_1_1_1_1: no inet address; ip route is empty.\\n  • host_2_1_1_1: no inet address; ip route is empty.\\n- From host_1_1_1_1 and host_2_1_1_1, ping to dns_server, load_balancer, web_server_0 fails immediately with “Network is unreachable,” consistent with having no IP/default route.\\n- curl from these hosts to http://web99.local and http://web0.local shows near-zero timing with no connect/TTFB, consistent with no network stack configuration or failure to resolve/connect.\\n\\n2) DHCP server is up and serving correct scopes, but relays are down\\n- DHCP server (10.200.0.8):\\n  • isc-dhcp-server service: Active (running).\\n  • dhcpd.conf includes scopes for all access VLANs (10.1.x.0/24 and 10.2.x.0/24) with option domain-name-servers 10.200.0.2.\\n- DHCP relay on distribution routers:\\n  • router_dist_1_1: isc-dhcp-relay service inactive (dead).\\n  • router_dist_2_1: isc-dhcp-relay service inactive (dead).\\n- Without active relays on the distribution layer, host broadcast DHCPDISCOVER frames are not forwarded to the centralized DHCP server, so hosts remain unconfigured (observed on both tested hosts).\\n\\n3) Server-farm network is not in OSPF; no route to 10.200.0.0/24 from campus\\n- server_access_router:\\n  • Interface br0 has 10.200.0.1/24; eth7 has 172.16.0.23/31 toward core_3.\\n  • FRR OSPF is present but has no network statements/areas configured, no neighbors, and has not run SPF (Number of areas: 0).\\n  • show ip route 10.200.0.0/24 shows connected only on server_access_router.\\n- Distribution and core routers:\\n  • router_dist_1_1 and router_dist_2_1: show ip route 10.200.0.0/24 -> “% Network not in table.”\\n  • router_core_1/2/3: show ip route 10.200.0.0/24 -> “% Network not in table.”\\n  • Dist routers have healthy OSPF adjacencies to the core and have learned other subnets via OSPF (routes to 10.1.x/10.2.x and 172.16.x present), indicating OSPF is functioning in the campus core/distribution – except for the server-farm side.\\n\\n4) Local server-farm connectivity is healthy\\n- Web servers and load balancer can ping the DHCP server within 10.200.0.0/24 successfully (low RTTs), showing the server-farm L2/L3 within 10.200.0.0/24 is fine.\\n\\nFault localization\\n- Devices directly implicated:\\n  • router_dist_1_1 and router_dist_2_1: DHCP relay services are not running (inactive/dead).\\n  • server_access_router: OSPF not configured to participate/advertise; no neighbors; not injecting 10.200.0.0/24 into OSPF.\\n- Impacted domains:\\n  • All access subnets under both distribution blocks (10.1.1.0/24 and 10.2.1.0/24 tested) cannot obtain DHCP leases.\\n  • The entire campus lacks a route to 10.200.0.0/24, isolating DHCP/DNS/Web services from end hosts and distribution/core devices.\\n\\nRoot cause analysis\\n- Immediate root cause for hosts lacking IP configuration: DHCP relay processes are not running on both distribution routers, preventing DHCP broadcasts from reaching the central DHCP server.\\n- Underlying routing/control-plane root cause: The server_access_router is not participating in OSPF (no networks/areas configured), so 10.200.0.0/24 is absent from the OSPF domain; consequently, even if DHCP relay were operational, distribution routers would still not have a route to 10.200.0.8 (DHCP server), and clients would not reach DNS/Web services in 10.200.0.0/24.\\n\\nOverall assessment\\n- Network is not meeting design intent. The combined failures (disabled DHCP relays and missing OSPF advertisement from the server-farm edge) break end-to-end service discovery and access:\\n  • Hosts cannot acquire addresses.\\n  • Core/distribution cannot route to the server farm.\\n  • Server-farm side remains locally healthy but isolated.\\n\\nNo remediation steps are provided here per request; this report focuses on detection, localization, and root cause identification., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='8eea97e9-0f40-47f7-9d81-cead9a08426a'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
